{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"We're here today to announce"},{"time":3000,"text":"the first synthetic cell,"},{"time":6000,"text":"a cell made by"},{"time":8000,"text":"starting with the digital code in the computer,"},{"time":11000,"text":"building the chromosome"},{"time":14000,"text":"from four bottles of chemicals,"},{"time":17000,"text":"assembling that chromosome in yeast,"},{"time":19000,"text":"transplanting it into"},{"time":22000,"text":"a recipient bacterial cell"},{"time":24000,"text":"and transforming that cell"},{"time":26000,"text":"into a new bacterial species."},{"time":29000,"text":"So this is the first self-replicating species"},{"time":32000,"text":"that we've had on the planet"},{"time":34000,"text":"whose parent is a computer."},{"time":37000,"text":"It also is the first species"},{"time":39000,"text":"to have its own website"},{"time":41000,"text":"encoded in its genetic code."},{"time":44000,"text":"But we'll talk more about"},{"time":46000,"text":"the watermarks in a minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49000,"text":"This is a project that had its inception"},{"time":51000,"text":"15 years ago"},{"time":53000,"text":"when our team then --"},{"time":55000,"text":"we called the institute TIGR --"},{"time":57000,"text":"was involved in sequencing"},{"time":59000,"text":"the first two genomes in history."},{"time":61000,"text":"We did Haemophilus influenzae"},{"time":63000,"text":"and then the smallest genome of a self-replicating organism,"},{"time":66000,"text":"that of Mycoplasma genitalium."},{"time":69000,"text":"And as soon as"},{"time":71000,"text":"we had these two sequences"},{"time":73000,"text":"we thought, if this is supposed to be the smallest genome"},{"time":76000,"text":"of a self-replicating species,"},{"time":78000,"text":"could there be even a smaller genome?"},{"time":80000,"text":"Could we understand the basis of cellular life"},{"time":83000,"text":"at the genetic level?"},{"time":85000,"text":"It's been a 15-year quest"},{"time":87000,"text":"just to get to the starting point now"},{"time":89000,"text":"to be able to answer those questions,"},{"time":92000,"text":"because it's very difficult to eliminate"},{"time":94000,"text":"multiple genes from a cell."},{"time":96000,"text":"You can only do them one at a time."},{"time":99000,"text":"We decided early on"},{"time":101000,"text":"that we had to take a synthetic route,"},{"time":103000,"text":"even though nobody had been there before,"},{"time":105000,"text":"to see if we could synthesize"},{"time":107000,"text":"a bacterial chromosome"},{"time":109000,"text":"so we could actually vary the gene content"},{"time":111000,"text":"to understand the essential genes for life."},{"time":114000,"text":"That started our 15-year quest"},{"time":117000,"text":"to get here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119000,"text":"But before we did the first experiments,"},{"time":121000,"text":"we actually asked"},{"time":124000,"text":"Art Caplan's team at the University of Pennsylvania"},{"time":127000,"text":"to undertake a review"},{"time":129000,"text":"of what the risks, the challenges,"},{"time":132000,"text":"the ethics around creating new"},{"time":134000,"text":"species in the laboratory were"},{"time":136000,"text":"because it hadn't been done before."},{"time":138000,"text":"They spent about two years"},{"time":140000,"text":"reviewing that independently"},{"time":142000,"text":"and published their results in Science in 1999."},{"time":145000,"text":"Ham and I took two years off"},{"time":147000,"text":"as a side project to sequence the human genome,"},{"time":149000,"text":"but as soon as that was done"},{"time":151000,"text":"we got back to the task at hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155000,"text":"In 2002, we started"},{"time":157000,"text":"a new institute,"},{"time":159000,"text":"the Institute for Biological Energy Alternatives,"},{"time":162000,"text":"where we set out two goals:"},{"time":164000,"text":"One, to understand"},{"time":166000,"text":"the impact of our technology on the environment,"},{"time":169000,"text":"and how to understand the environment better,"},{"time":171000,"text":"and two, to start down this process"},{"time":173000,"text":"of making synthetic life"},{"time":176000,"text":"to understand basic life."},{"time":179000,"text":"In 2003,"},{"time":181000,"text":"we published our first success."},{"time":183000,"text":"So Ham Smith and Clyde Hutchison"},{"time":185000,"text":"developed some new methods"},{"time":187000,"text":"for making error-free DNA"},{"time":190000,"text":"at a small level."},{"time":192000,"text":"Our first task was"},{"time":194000,"text":"a 5,000-letter code bacteriophage,"},{"time":197000,"text":"a virus that attacks only E. coli."},{"time":201000,"text":"So that was"},{"time":203000,"text":"the phage phi X 174,"},{"time":205000,"text":"which was chosen for historical reasons."},{"time":207000,"text":"It was the first DNA phage,"},{"time":210000,"text":"DNA virus, DNA genome"},{"time":213000,"text":"that was actually sequenced."},{"time":215000,"text":"So once we realized"},{"time":218000,"text":"that we could make 5,000-base pair"},{"time":220000,"text":"viral-sized pieces,"},{"time":222000,"text":"we thought, we at least have the means"},{"time":224000,"text":"then to try and make serially lots of these pieces"},{"time":227000,"text":"to be able to eventually assemble them together"},{"time":230000,"text":"to make this mega base chromosome."},{"time":234000,"text":"So, substantially larger than"},{"time":236000,"text":"we even thought we would go initially."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240000,"text":"There were several steps to this. There were two sides:"},{"time":243000,"text":"We had to solve the chemistry"},{"time":245000,"text":"for making large DNA molecules,"},{"time":247000,"text":"and we had to solve the biological side"},{"time":249000,"text":"of how, if we had this new chemical entity,"},{"time":252000,"text":"how would we boot it up, activate it"},{"time":255000,"text":"in a recipient cell."},{"time":258000,"text":"We had two teams working in parallel:"},{"time":260000,"text":"one team on the chemistry,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and the other on trying to"},{"time":265000,"text":"be able to transplant"},{"time":267000,"text":"entire chromosomes"},{"time":269000,"text":"to get new cells."},{"time":272000,"text":"When we started this out, we thought the synthesis would be the biggest problem,"},{"time":275000,"text":"which is why we chose the smallest genome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278000,"text":"And some of you have noticed that we switched from the smallest genome"},{"time":281000,"text":"to a much larger one."},{"time":283000,"text":"And we can walk through the reasons for that,"},{"time":285000,"text":"but basically the small cell"},{"time":288000,"text":"took on the order of"},{"time":290000,"text":"one to two months to get results from,"},{"time":293000,"text":"whereas the larger, faster-growing cell"},{"time":295000,"text":"takes only two days."},{"time":297000,"text":"So there's only so many cycles we could go through"},{"time":300000,"text":"in a year at six weeks per cycle."},{"time":303000,"text":"And you should know that basically"},{"time":305000,"text":"99, probably 99 percent plus"},{"time":308000,"text":"of our experiments failed."},{"time":310000,"text":"So this was a debugging,"},{"time":312000,"text":"problem-solving scenario from the beginning"},{"time":315000,"text":"because there was no recipe"},{"time":317000,"text":"of how to get there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"So, one of the most important publications we had"},{"time":322000,"text":"was in 2007."},{"time":324000,"text":"Carole Lartigue led the effort"},{"time":327000,"text":"to actually transplant a bacterial chromosome"},{"time":330000,"text":"from one bacteria to another."},{"time":332000,"text":"I think philosophically, that was one of the most important papers"},{"time":335000,"text":"that we've ever done"},{"time":337000,"text":"because it showed how dynamic life was."},{"time":340000,"text":"And we knew, once that worked,"},{"time":342000,"text":"that we actually had a chance"},{"time":344000,"text":"if we could make the synthetic chromosomes"},{"time":346000,"text":"to do the same with those."},{"time":349000,"text":"We didn't know that it was going to take us"},{"time":351000,"text":"several years more to get there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353000,"text":"In 2008,"},{"time":355000,"text":"we reported the complete synthesis"},{"time":357000,"text":"of the Mycoplasma genitalium genome,"},{"time":360000,"text":"a little over 500,000 letters of genetic code,"},{"time":364000,"text":"but we have not yet succeeded in booting up that chromosome."},{"time":367000,"text":"We think in part, because of its slow growth"},{"time":371000,"text":"and, in part,"},{"time":373000,"text":"cells have all kinds of unique defense mechanisms"},{"time":376000,"text":"to keep these events from happening."},{"time":378000,"text":"It turned out the cell that we were trying to transplant into"},{"time":381000,"text":"had a nuclease, an enzyme that chews up DNA on its surface,"},{"time":384000,"text":"and was happy to eat"},{"time":386000,"text":"the synthetic DNA that we gave it"},{"time":388000,"text":"and never got transplantations."},{"time":391000,"text":"But at the time, that was the largest"},{"time":393000,"text":"molecule of a defined structure"},{"time":395000,"text":"that had been made."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397000,"text":"And so both sides were progressing,"},{"time":399000,"text":"but part of the synthesis"},{"time":401000,"text":"had to be accomplished or was able to be accomplished"},{"time":404000,"text":"using yeast, putting the fragments in yeast"},{"time":407000,"text":"and yeast would assemble these for us."},{"time":409000,"text":"It's an amazing step forward,"},{"time":412000,"text":"but we had a problem because now we had"},{"time":414000,"text":"the bacterial chromosomes growing in yeast."},{"time":417000,"text":"So in addition to doing the transplant,"},{"time":420000,"text":"we had to find out how to get a bacterial chromosome"},{"time":422000,"text":"out of the eukaryotic yeast"},{"time":424000,"text":"into a form where we could transplant it"},{"time":426000,"text":"into a recipient cell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430000,"text":"So our team developed new techniques"},{"time":433000,"text":"for actually growing, cloning"},{"time":435000,"text":"entire bacterial chromosomes in yeast."},{"time":437000,"text":"So we took the same mycoides genome"},{"time":440000,"text":"that Carole had initially transplanted,"},{"time":442000,"text":"and we grew that in yeast"},{"time":444000,"text":"as an artificial chromosome."},{"time":447000,"text":"And we thought this would be a great test bed"},{"time":449000,"text":"for learning how to get chromosomes out of yeast"},{"time":451000,"text":"and transplant them."},{"time":453000,"text":"When we did these experiments, though,"},{"time":455000,"text":"we could get the chromosome out of yeast"},{"time":457000,"text":"but it wouldn't transplant and boot up a cell."},{"time":461000,"text":"That little issue took the team two years to solve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"It turns out, the DNA in the bacterial cell"},{"time":467000,"text":"was actually methylated,"},{"time":469000,"text":"and the methylation protects it from the restriction enzyme,"},{"time":473000,"text":"from digesting the DNA."},{"time":476000,"text":"So what we found is if we took the chromosome"},{"time":478000,"text":"out of yeast and methylated it,"},{"time":480000,"text":"we could then transplant it."},{"time":482000,"text":"Further advances came"},{"time":484000,"text":"when the team removed the restriction enzyme genes"},{"time":487000,"text":"from the recipient capricolum cell."},{"time":490000,"text":"And once we had done that, now we can take"},{"time":492000,"text":"naked DNA out of yeast and transplant it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495000,"text":"So last fall"},{"time":497000,"text":"when we published the results of that work in Science,"},{"time":500000,"text":"we all became overconfident"},{"time":502000,"text":"and were sure we were only"},{"time":504000,"text":"a few weeks away"},{"time":506000,"text":"from being able to now boot up"},{"time":508000,"text":"a chromosome out of yeast."},{"time":511000,"text":"Because of the problems with"},{"time":513000,"text":"Mycoplasma genitalium and its slow growth"},{"time":516000,"text":"about a year and a half ago,"},{"time":519000,"text":"we decided to synthesize"},{"time":522000,"text":"the much larger chromosome, the mycoides chromosome,"},{"time":525000,"text":"knowing that we had the biology worked out on that"},{"time":528000,"text":"for transplantation."},{"time":530000,"text":"And Dan led the team for the synthesis"},{"time":532000,"text":"of this over one-million-base pair chromosome."},{"time":537000,"text":"But it turned out it wasn't going to be as simple in the end,"},{"time":540000,"text":"and it set us back three months"},{"time":542000,"text":"because we had one error"},{"time":544000,"text":"out of over a million base pairs in that sequence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547000,"text":"So the team developed new debugging software,"},{"time":550000,"text":"where we could test each synthetic fragment"},{"time":553000,"text":"to see if it would grow in a background"},{"time":555000,"text":"of wild type DNA."},{"time":558000,"text":"And we found that 10 out of the 11"},{"time":561000,"text":"100,000-base pair pieces we synthesized"},{"time":564000,"text":"were completely accurate"},{"time":566000,"text":"and compatible with"},{"time":568000,"text":"a life-forming sequence."},{"time":572000,"text":"We narrowed it down to one fragment;"},{"time":574000,"text":"we sequenced it"},{"time":576000,"text":"and found just one base pair had been deleted"},{"time":578000,"text":"in an essential gene."},{"time":580000,"text":"So accuracy is essential."},{"time":583000,"text":"There's parts of the genome"},{"time":585000,"text":"where it cannot tolerate even a single error,"},{"time":588000,"text":"and then there's parts of the genome"},{"time":590000,"text":"where we can put in large blocks of DNA,"},{"time":592000,"text":"as we did with the watermarks,"},{"time":594000,"text":"and it can tolerate all kinds of errors."},{"time":597000,"text":"So it took about three months to find that error"},{"time":600000,"text":"and repair it."},{"time":602000,"text":"And then early one morning, at 6 a.m."},{"time":605000,"text":"we got a text from Dan"},{"time":608000,"text":"saying that, now, the first blue colonies existed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"So, it's been a long route to get here:"},{"time":614000,"text":"15 years from the beginning."},{"time":617000,"text":"We felt"},{"time":619000,"text":"one of the tenets of this field"},{"time":621000,"text":"was to make absolutely certain"},{"time":624000,"text":"we could distinguish synthetic DNA"},{"time":627000,"text":"from natural DNA."},{"time":629000,"text":"Early on, when you're working in a new area of science,"},{"time":632000,"text":"you have to think about all the pitfalls"},{"time":635000,"text":"and things that could lead you"},{"time":637000,"text":"to believe that you had done something when you hadn't,"},{"time":640000,"text":"and, even worse, leading others to believe it."},{"time":643000,"text":"So, we thought the worst problem would be"},{"time":645000,"text":"a single molecule contamination"},{"time":648000,"text":"of the native chromosome,"},{"time":650000,"text":"leading us to believe that we actually had"},{"time":653000,"text":"created a synthetic cell,"},{"time":655000,"text":"when it would have been just a contaminant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657000,"text":"So early on, we developed the notion"},{"time":659000,"text":"of putting in watermarks in the DNA"},{"time":661000,"text":"to absolutely make clear"},{"time":663000,"text":"that the DNA was synthetic."},{"time":666000,"text":"And the first chromosome we built"},{"time":669000,"text":"in 2008 --"},{"time":671000,"text":"the 500,000-base pair one --"},{"time":673000,"text":"we simply assigned"},{"time":676000,"text":"the names of the authors of the chromosome"},{"time":679000,"text":"into the genetic code,"},{"time":682000,"text":"but it was using just amino acid"},{"time":684000,"text":"single letter translations,"},{"time":686000,"text":"which leaves out certain letters of the alphabet."},{"time":690000,"text":"So the team actually developed a new code"},{"time":693000,"text":"within the code within the code."},{"time":696000,"text":"So it's a new code"},{"time":698000,"text":"for interpreting and writing messages in DNA."},{"time":701000,"text":"Now, mathematicians have been hiding and writing"},{"time":704000,"text":"messages in the genetic code for a long time,"},{"time":707000,"text":"but it's clear they were mathematicians and not biologists"},{"time":710000,"text":"because, if you write long messages"},{"time":713000,"text":"with the code that the mathematicians developed,"},{"time":716000,"text":"it would more than likely lead to"},{"time":718000,"text":"new proteins being synthesized"},{"time":721000,"text":"with unknown functions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724000,"text":"So the code that Mike Montague and the team developed"},{"time":727000,"text":"actually puts frequent stop codons,"},{"time":729000,"text":"so it's a different alphabet"},{"time":732000,"text":"but allows us to use"},{"time":734000,"text":"the entire English alphabet"},{"time":737000,"text":"with punctuation and numbers."},{"time":739000,"text":"So, there are four major watermarks"},{"time":741000,"text":"all over 1,000 base pairs of genetic code."},{"time":744000,"text":"The first one actually contains within it"},{"time":747000,"text":"this code for interpreting"},{"time":750000,"text":"the rest of the genetic code."},{"time":754000,"text":"So in the remaining information,"},{"time":756000,"text":"in the watermarks,"},{"time":758000,"text":"contain the names of, I think it's"},{"time":761000,"text":"46 different authors"},{"time":763000,"text":"and key contributors"},{"time":765000,"text":"to getting the project to this stage."},{"time":769000,"text":"And we also built in"},{"time":771000,"text":"a website address"},{"time":774000,"text":"so that if somebody decodes the code"},{"time":776000,"text":"within the code within the code,"},{"time":778000,"text":"they can send an email to that address."},{"time":780000,"text":"So it's clearly distinguishable"},{"time":783000,"text":"from any other species,"},{"time":785000,"text":"having 46 names in it,"},{"time":788000,"text":"its own web address."},{"time":792000,"text":"And we added three quotations,"},{"time":795000,"text":"because with the first genome"},{"time":797000,"text":"we were criticized for not trying to say something more profound"},{"time":800000,"text":"than just signing the work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802000,"text":"So we won't give the rest of the code,"},{"time":804000,"text":"but we will give the three quotations."},{"time":806000,"text":"The first is,"},{"time":808000,"text":"\"To live, to err,"},{"time":810000,"text":"to fall, to triumph"},{"time":812000,"text":"and to recreate life out of life.\""},{"time":814000,"text":"It's a James Joyce quote."},{"time":818000,"text":"The second quotation is, \"See things not as they are,"},{"time":821000,"text":"but as they might be.\""},{"time":823000,"text":"It's a quote from the \"American Prometheus\""},{"time":826000,"text":"book on Robert Oppenheimer."},{"time":828000,"text":"And the last one is a Richard Feynman quote:"},{"time":831000,"text":"\"What I cannot build,"},{"time":833000,"text":"I cannot understand.\""},{"time":838000,"text":"So, because this is as much a philosophical advance"},{"time":841000,"text":"as a technical advance in science,"},{"time":844000,"text":"we tried to deal with both the philosophical"},{"time":847000,"text":"and the technical side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"The last thing I want to say before turning it over to questions"},{"time":851000,"text":"is that the extensive work"},{"time":854000,"text":"that we've done --"},{"time":856000,"text":"asking for ethical review,"},{"time":858000,"text":"pushing the envelope"},{"time":860000,"text":"on that side as well as the technical side --"},{"time":863000,"text":"this has been broadly discussed in the scientific community,"},{"time":866000,"text":"in the policy community"},{"time":868000,"text":"and at the highest levels of the federal government."},{"time":871000,"text":"Even with this announcement,"},{"time":874000,"text":"as we did in 2003 --"},{"time":876000,"text":"that work was funded by the Department of Energy,"},{"time":879000,"text":"so the work was reviewed"},{"time":881000,"text":"at the level of the White House,"},{"time":883000,"text":"trying to decide whether to classify the work or publish it."},{"time":886000,"text":"And they came down on the side of open publication,"},{"time":889000,"text":"which is the right approach --"},{"time":892000,"text":"we've briefed the White House,"},{"time":894000,"text":"we've briefed members of Congress,"},{"time":897000,"text":"we've tried to take and push"},{"time":899000,"text":"the policy issues"},{"time":901000,"text":"in parallel with the scientific advances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905000,"text":"So with that, I would like"},{"time":907000,"text":"to open it first to the floor for questions."},{"time":910000,"text":"Yes, in the back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912000,"text":"Reporter: Could you explain, in layman's terms,"},{"time":914000,"text":"how significant a breakthrough this is please?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":918000,"text":"Craig Venter: Can we explain how significant this is?"},{"time":920000,"text":"I'm not sure we're the ones that should be explaining how significant it is."},{"time":923000,"text":"It's significant to us."},{"time":926000,"text":"Perhaps it's a giant philosophical change"},{"time":929000,"text":"in how we view life."},{"time":931000,"text":"We actually view it as a baby step in terms of,"},{"time":934000,"text":"it's taken us 15 years to be able"},{"time":936000,"text":"to do the experiment"},{"time":938000,"text":"we wanted to do 15 years ago"},{"time":940000,"text":"on understanding life at its basic level."},{"time":943000,"text":"But we actually believe"},{"time":945000,"text":"this is going to be a very powerful set of tools"},{"time":949000,"text":"and we're already starting"},{"time":951000,"text":"in numerous avenues"},{"time":953000,"text":"to use this tool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955000,"text":"We have, at the Institute,"},{"time":957000,"text":"ongoing funding now from NIH"},{"time":960000,"text":"in a program with Novartis"},{"time":962000,"text":"to try and use these new"},{"time":964000,"text":"synthetic DNA tools"},{"time":966000,"text":"to perhaps make the flu vaccine"},{"time":969000,"text":"that you might get next year."},{"time":972000,"text":"Because instead of taking weeks to months to make these,"},{"time":975000,"text":"Dan's team can now make these"},{"time":978000,"text":"in less than 24 hours."},{"time":981000,"text":"So when you see how long it took to get an H1N1 vaccine out,"},{"time":984000,"text":"we think we can shorten that process"},{"time":986000,"text":"quite substantially."},{"time":988000,"text":"In the vaccine area,"},{"time":990000,"text":"Synthetic Genomics and the Institute"},{"time":992000,"text":"are forming a new vaccine company"},{"time":994000,"text":"because we think these tools can affect vaccines"},{"time":997000,"text":"to diseases that haven't been possible to date,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"things where the viruses rapidly evolve,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"such with rhinovirus."},{"time":1005000,"text":"Wouldn't it be nice to have something that actually blocked common colds?"},{"time":1008000,"text":"Or, more importantly, HIV,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"where the virus evolves so quickly"},{"time":1013000,"text":"the vaccines that are made today"},{"time":1015000,"text":"can't keep up"},{"time":1017000,"text":"with those evolutionary changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020000,"text":"Also, at Synthetic Genomics,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"we've been working"},{"time":1024000,"text":"on major environmental issues."},{"time":1026000,"text":"I think this latest oil spill in the Gulf"},{"time":1028000,"text":"is a reminder."},{"time":1030000,"text":"We can't see CO2 --"},{"time":1032000,"text":"we depend on scientific measurements for it"},{"time":1034000,"text":"and we see the beginning results"},{"time":1036000,"text":"of having too much of it --"},{"time":1038000,"text":"but we can see pre-CO2 now"},{"time":1040000,"text":"floating on the waters"},{"time":1042000,"text":"and contaminating the beaches in the Gulf."},{"time":1045000,"text":"We need some alternatives"},{"time":1048000,"text":"for oil."},{"time":1050000,"text":"We have a program with Exxon Mobile"},{"time":1052000,"text":"to try and develop new strains of algae"},{"time":1055000,"text":"that can efficiently capture carbon dioxide"},{"time":1058000,"text":"from the atmosphere or from concentrated sources,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"make new hydrocarbons that can go into their refineries"},{"time":1064000,"text":"to make normal gasoline"},{"time":1066000,"text":"and diesel fuel out of CO2."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068000,"text":"Those are just a couple of the approaches"},{"time":1070000,"text":"and directions that we're taking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1073000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}